==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Punchinello
<hw>Pun`chi*nel"lo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.
<ets>pulcinella</ets>, probably originally a word of endearment, dim. of
<ets>pulcina</ets>, <ets>pulcino</ets>, a chicken, from L.
<ets>pullicenus</ets>, <ets>pullus</ets>. See <er>Pullet</er>.]</ety>
<def>A punch; a buffoon; originally, in a puppet show, a character
represented as fat, short, and humpbacked.</def>
<rj><au>Spectator.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Punchy</ent>⟦br⟧
